      <p>
        <strong>Hi, I’m Will!</strong> I’m passionate about <strong>creative design</strong>: fine art, photography, graphic design, and film &amp; video production. Raised in England, I’ve created art since I was young—always curious about new ways to express ideas.
      </p>
      <p>
        As a self-taught image editor, I started with free tools like <strong>Pixlr E</strong> and <strong>PicsArt</strong> on my phone. In school and college, I developed my <strong>Adobe Suite</strong> skills for editing, manipulation, digital drawing, and video production. I mostly use <span style="color:var(--accent-main);"><strong>Photoshop</strong></span> for illustration and edits, sometimes <strong>Illustrator</strong> for graphics, and <strong>Premiere Pro</strong> for film/video. I’m learning <strong>Adobe Animate</strong> for animation and use <strong>Procreate</strong> on my iPad for concept art and digital painting.
      </p>
      <p>
        Recent photography and videography have been shot on my Canon EOS 2000D, but I’m now making the most of my iPhone 14 until I can upgrade my camera. I’ve explored traditional mediums forever: pencil/ink drawing, watercolours, oils, acrylics, monoprinting, cyanotypes, and more.
      </p>
      <p>
